{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884136163,"sessionID":"ses_285115a2effeS82cuMfDq5cS4K","part":{"id":"prt_d7af16e70001gukY1aDIw2lW5V","messageID":"msg_d7aef6b88001m9tUtTXK1qOuQX","sessionID":"ses_285115a2effeS82cuMfDq5cS4K","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f9af1642e3f142af98972ff34741bfb6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-033\n- **Title**: Makefile 构建目标体系\n- **Module**: root\n- **Language**: Makefile\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Makefile build target system in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for a unified build system that manages building, testing, cleaning, code quality checks, and Docker image builds for both Go and Python components. The specification ensures a standardized, efficient, and developer-friendly build interface with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to verify proper implementation of all build targets and features.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Makefile structure and organization\n\nThe system SHALL implement a modular Makefile structure with a main Makefile in the root directory and organized sub-Makefiles for different language and functional areas.\n\n#### Scenario: Root Makefile exists and is properly structured\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project root directory\n- **WHEN** examining the directory structure\n- **THEN** a Makefile SHALL exist in the root directory\n- **AND** the Makefile SHALL be the main entry point for all build operations\n- **AND** the Makefile SHALL include sub-Makefiles from .makefiles/ directory\n\n#### Scenario: .makefiles/ directory exists with sub-Makefiles\n- **GIVEN** the .makefiles/ directory\n- **WHEN** examining its contents\n- **THEN** go.mk SHALL exist for Go-specific build rules\n- **AND** python.mk SHALL exist for Python-specific build rules\n- **AND** docker.mk SHALL exist for Docker-specific build rules\n- **AND** test.mk SHALL exist for test-specific rules\n- **AND** lint.mk SHALL exist for lint/format-specific rules\n- **AND** each sub-Makefile SHALL be properly included in the main Makefile\n\n#### Scenario: scripts/ directory exists for build scripts\n- **GIVEN** the scripts/ directory\n- **WHEN** examining its contents\n- **THEN** build.sh SHALL exist for complex build operations\n- **AND** test.sh SHALL exist for test execution scripts\n- **AND** release.sh SHALL exist for release preparation scripts\n- **AND** scripts SHALL be executable (chmod +x)\n\n#### Scenario: bin/ directory exists for build artifacts\n- **GIVEN** the bin/ directory\n- **WHEN** examining its structure\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL exist or be created on first build\n- **AND** the directory SHALL be in .gitignore\n- **AND** build artifacts SHALL be placed in bin/ by default\n- **AND** cross-platform artifacts SHALL be placed in bin/<platform>/ subdirectories\n\n### Requirement: Go build targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive build targets for all Go binaries in the AgentCube project.\n\n#### Scenario: build-go target builds all Go binaries\n- **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project with Go source code\n- **WHEN** running `make build-go`\n- **THEN** all Go binaries SHALL be compiled successfully\n- **AND** binaries SHALL be placed in bin/ directory\n- **AND** the following binaries SHALL be built: agentd, picod, cli\n- **AND** build status SHALL be displayed with color-coded output\n\n#### Scenario: build target builds both Go and Python components\n- **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make build`\n- **THEN** `make build-go` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make build-python` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** both Go and Python artifacts SHALL be built successfully\n- **AND** the build SHALL complete without errors\n\n#### Scenario: Individual Go component build targets exist\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile Go targets\n- **WHEN** examining the available targets\n- **THEN** build-agentd target SHALL exist\n- **AND** build-picod target SHALL exist\n- **AND** build-router target SHALL exist (if router exists)\n- **AND** build-cli target SHALL exist\n- **AND** each target SHALL build only its respective component\n\n#### Scenario: build-agentd target builds agentd binary\n- **GIVEN** the agentd source code in cmd/agentd/\n- **WHEN** running `make build-agentd`\n- **THEN** agentd binary SHALL be compiled\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/agentd\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n- **AND** build metadata (version, commit) SHALL be embedded\n\n#### Scenario: build-picod target builds picod binary\n- **GIVEN** the picod source code in cmd/picod/\n- **WHEN** running `make build-picod`\n- **THEN** picod binary SHALL be compiled\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/picod\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n- **AND** build metadata SHALL be embedded\n\n#### Scenario: build-cli target builds CLI tool\n- **GIVEN** the CLI source code in cmd/cli/\n- **WHEN** running `make build-cli`\n- **THEN** CLI binary SHALL be compiled\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/agentcube\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n- **AND** the binary SHALL respond to --version flag\n\n#### Scenario: Go build supports cross-platform compilation\n- **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n- **WHEN** setting GOOS and GOARCH environment variables\n- **THEN** the build SHALL compile for the target platform\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be placed in bin/<platform>/ subdirectory\n- **AND** supported platforms SHALL include: linux/amd64, linux/arm64, darwin/amd64, darwin/arm64\n\n#### Scenario: Go build supports release mode\n- **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n- **WHEN** setting BUILD_MODE=release\n- **THEN** build flags SHALL include -ldflags=\"-s -w\" for stripping\n- **AND** debug information SHALL be removed\n- **AND** the binary size SHALL be minimized\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be production-ready\n\n#### Scenario: Go build supports dev mode with race detection\n- **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n- **WHEN** setting BUILD_MODE=dev (default)\n- **THEN** build flags SHALL include -race for race detection\n- **AND** debug information SHALL be included\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be suitable for development\n\n#### Scenario: Go build uses build cache efficiently\n- **GIVEN** a previous successful build\n- **WHEN** running `make build-go` again without source changes\n- **THEN** the build SHALL use cached artifacts\n- **AND** the build time SHALL be significantly faster\n- **AND** \"cache hit\" messages SHALL be displayed\n\n### Requirement: Python build targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive build targets for Python packages in the AgentCube project.\n\n#### Scenario: build-python target builds Python package\n- **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project with Python source code\n- **WHEN** running `make build-python`\n- **THEN** the Python package SHALL be built as wheel\n- **AND** the wheel SHALL be placed in dist/ directory\n- **AND** the source distribution (sdist) SHALL also be built\n- **AND** build SHALL complete successfully\n\n#### Scenario: install-python target installs Python dependencies\n- **GIVEN** a Python environment with pip\n- **WHEN** running `make install-python`\n- **THEN** all production dependencies SHALL be installed\n- **AND** dependencies SHALL be read from requirements.txt or pyproject.toml\n- **AND** installation SHALL complete without errors\n- **AND** installed packages SHALL be listed\n\n#### Scenario: install-dev target installs development dependencies\n- **GIVEN** a Python environment with pip\n- **WHEN** running `make install-dev`\n- **THEN** all development dependencies SHALL be installed\n- **AND** dependencies SHALL include: pytest, ruff, mypy, black\n- **AND** installation SHALL complete without errors\n- **AND** development environment SHALL be ready\n\n#### Scenario: Python build uses virtual environment\n- **GIVEN** the Python build targets\n- **WHEN** VIRTUAL_ENV environment variable is set\n- **THEN** the build SHALL use the virtual environment's Python\n- **AND** packages SHALL be installed in the virtual environment\n- **AND** the virtual environment SHALL not be affected by system Python\n\n#### Scenario: Python build respects PYTHON_VERSION variable\n- **GIVEN** the Python build targets\n- **WHEN** setting PYTHON_VERSION to a specific version (e.g., 3.11)\n- **THEN** the build SHALL use the specified Python version\n- **AND** the version SHALL be validated\n- **AND** an error SHALL occur if the version is not available\n\n### Requirement: Test targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive test targets for running Go and Python tests.\n\n#### Scenario: test target runs all tests\n- **GIVEN** a built AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make test`\n- **THEN** `make test-go` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make test-python` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** all tests SHALL pass\n- **AND** test summary SHALL be displayed with pass/fail counts\n\n#### Scenario: test-go target runs Go tests\n- **GIVEN** the Go source code with tests\n- **WHEN** running `make test-go`\n- **THEN** all Go tests SHALL be executed\n- **AND** tests SHALL run with verbose output (-v flag)\n- **AND** test coverage SHALL be collected\n- **AND** test results SHALL be summarized\n\n#### Scenario: test-python target runs Python tests\n- **GIVEN** the Python source code with tests\n- **WHEN** running `make test-python`\n- **THEN** all Python tests SHALL be executed using pytest\n- **AND** tests SHALL run with verbose output\n- **AND** test coverage SHALL be collected\n- **AND** test results SHALL be summarized\n\n#### Scenario: test-integration target runs integration tests\n- **GIVEN** the integration test suite\n- **WHEN** running `make test-integration`\n- **THEN** integration tests SHALL be executed\n- **AND** required services SHALL be started (if needed)\n- **AND** tests SHALL verify end-to-end functionality\n- **AND** test results SHALL be summarized\n\n#### Scenario: test-coverage target generates coverage reports\n- **GIVEN** the test suite with coverage enabled\n- **WHEN** running `make test-coverage`\n- **THEN** test coverage SHALL be collected for Go\n- **AND** test coverage SHALL be collected for Python\n- **AND** coverage reports SHALL be generated\n- **AND** coverage percentage SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** coverage SHALL meet the minimum threshold (e.g., 70%)\n\n#### Scenario: test-race target runs Go tests with race detection\n- **GIVEN** the Go source code with tests\n- **WHEN** running `make test-race`\n- **THEN** tests SHALL run with -race flag enabled\n- **AND** race conditions SHALL be detected if present\n- **AND** test execution SHALL complete (slower than normal tests)\n- **AND** no race conditions SHALL be reported in a healthy codebase\n\n#### Scenario: Tests can be run with specific package paths\n- **GIVEN** the test targets\n- **WHEN** specifying a package path (e.g., make test-go PKG=./pkg/router)\n- **THEN** only tests in the specified package SHALL run\n- **AND** the package path SHALL be validated\n- **AND** test results SHALL be displayed for the specified package\n\n#### Scenario: Tests support parallel execution\n- **GIVEN** the test targets\n- **WHEN** running with -j flag (make -j test)\n- **THEN** Go and Python tests SHALL run in parallel\n- **AND** test execution SHALL complete faster\n- **AND** no test interference SHALL occur\n- **AND** test results SHALL be aggregated correctly\n\n### Requirement: Code quality targets (lint, format)\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive code quality targets for linting and formatting code.\n\n#### Scenario: lint target runs all lint checks\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with source code\n- **WHEN** running `make lint`\n- **THEN** `make lint-go` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make lint-python` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** all lint checks SHALL pass\n- **AND** lint summary SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: lint-go target runs Go lint checks\n- **GIVEN** the Go source code\n- **WHEN** running `make lint-go`\n- **THEN** golangci-lint SHALL be executed\n- **AND** all Go files SHALL be checked\n- **AND** lint errors SHALL be reported with file and line numbers\n- **AND** exit code SHALL be non-zero if lint errors exist\n\n#### Scenario: lint-python target runs Python lint checks\n- **GIVEN** the Python source code\n- **WHEN** running `make lint-python`\n- **THEN** ruff SHALL be executed for linting\n- **AND** all Python files SHALL be checked\n- **AND** lint errors SHALL be reported with file and line numbers\n- **AND** exit code SHALL be non-zero if lint errors exist\n\n#### Scenario: format target formats all code\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with source code\n- **WHEN** running `make format`\n- **THEN** `make format-go` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make format-python` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** all code SHALL be formatted according to standards\n- **AND** formatting summary SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: format-go target formats Go code\n- **GIVEN** the Go source code\n- **WHEN** running `make format-go`\n- **THEN** goimports SHALL be executed\n- **AND** imports SHALL be organized and sorted\n- **AND** code SHALL be formatted with gofmt standards\n- **AND** modified files SHALL be listed\n\n#### Scenario: format-python target formats Python code\n- **GIVEN** the Python source code\n- **WHEN** running `make format-python`\n- **THEN** black SHALL be executed\n- **AND** code SHALL be formatted according to PEP 8\n- **AND** modified files SHALL be listed\n- **AND** no formatting changes SHALL be made if code is already formatted\n\n#### Scenario: check target runs all quality checks\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make check`\n- **THEN** `make lint` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make test` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** all checks SHALL pass\n- **AND** comprehensive status SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: Lint and format targets support specific files\n- **GIVEN** the lint and format targets\n- **WHEN** specifying specific files (e.g., make lint-go FILES=cmd/agentd/main.go)\n- **THEN** only the specified files SHALL be checked/formatted\n- **AND** file paths SHALL be validated\n- **AND** results SHALL be displayed for the specified files\n\n### Requirement: Clean targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive clean targets for removing build artifacts and caches.\n\n#### Scenario: clean target removes build artifacts\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with build artifacts\n- **WHEN** running `make clean`\n- **THEN** `make clean-go` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make clean-python` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** build artifacts SHALL be removed\n- **AND** clean summary SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: clean-go target removes Go build artifacts\n- **GIVEN** Go build artifacts in bin/ directory\n- **WHEN** running `make clean-go`\n- **THEN** all Go binaries SHALL be removed from bin/\n- **AND** cross-platform artifacts SHALL be removed from bin/<platform>/\n- **AND** clean confirmation SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: clean-python target removes Python build artifacts\n- **GIVEN** Python build artifacts in dist/ directory\n- **WHEN** running `make clean-python`\n- **THEN** all wheel and sdist files SHALL be removed\n- **AND** __pycache__ directories SHALL be removed\n- **AND** .pyc files SHALL be removed\n- **AND** clean confirmation SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: clean-docker target removes Docker resources\n- **GIVEN** Docker images and containers built by the project\n- **WHEN** running `make clean-docker`\n- **THEN** project Docker containers SHALL be stopped and removed\n- **AND** project Docker images SHALL be removed\n- **AND** dangling images SHALL be pruned\n- **AND** clean confirmation SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: clean-all target removes all artifacts and caches\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with all build artifacts and caches\n- **WHEN** running `make clean-all`\n- **THEN** `make clean` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make clean-docker` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** build caches SHALL be cleared\n- **AND** temporary files SHALL be removed\n- **AND** the project SHALL be in a clean state\n\n#### Scenario: Clean targets use .NOTPARALLEL for safety\n- **GIVEN** the clean targets\n- **WHEN** running clean targets\n- **THEN** clean operations SHALL run sequentially\n- **AND** .NOTPARALLEL SHALL be specified for clean targets\n- **AND** no race conditions SHALL occur during cleanup\n\n### Requirement: Docker build targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive Docker build targets that integrate with the multi-stage Dockerfile from AR-032.\n\n#### Scenario: docker-build target builds Docker images\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile in the project root\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build`\n- **THEN** Docker images SHALL be built using multi-stage builds\n- **AND** builder, verifier, and runtime images SHALL be built\n- **AND** images SHALL be tagged with IMAGE_NAME:IMAGE_TAG\n- **AND** build progress SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: docker-build-builder target builds builder image\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile with builder stage\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build-builder`\n- **THEN** only the builder stage SHALL be built\n- **AND** the image SHALL be tagged with :builder suffix\n- **AND** build tools SHALL be included\n- **AND** build SHALL complete successfully\n\n#### Scenario: docker-build-runtime target builds runtime image\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile with runtime stage\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build-runtime`\n- **THEN** only the runtime stage SHALL be built\n- **AND** the image SHALL be minimal and production-ready\n- **AND** build tools SHALL NOT be included\n- **AND** build SHALL complete successfully\n\n#### Scenario: docker-push target pushes images to registry\n- **GIVEN** built Docker images\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-push` with DOCKER_REGISTRY set\n- **THEN** images SHALL be tagged with the registry prefix\n- **AND** images SHALL be pushed to the registry\n- **AND** push progress SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** push SHALL complete successfully\n\n#### Scenario: docker-tag target adds additional tags to images\n- **GIVEN** built Docker images\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-tag NEW_TAG=v1.0.0`\n- **THEN** images SHALL be tagged with the new tag\n- **AND** the original tag SHALL be preserved\n- **AND** tag confirmation SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build respects IMAGE_NAME and IMAGE_TAG variables\n- **GIVEN** the Docker build targets\n- **WHEN** setting IMAGE_NAME=myapp and IMAGE_TAG=latest\n- **THEN** images SHALL be built with name myapp\n- **AND** images SHALL be tagged with latest\n- **AND** variables SHALL be used consistently across all Docker targets\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build supports multi-architecture\n- **GIVEN** the Docker build targets\n- **WHEN** setting PLATFORMS=linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n- **THEN** images SHALL be built for both architectures\n- **AND** buildx SHALL be used for multi-arch builds\n- **AND** a manifest list SHALL be created\n- **AND** both architectures SHALL be available\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build integrates with AR-032 multi-stage builds\n- **GIVEN** the multi-stage Dockerfile from AR-032\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build`\n- **THEN** the three-stage build (builder, verifier, runtime) SHALL be used\n- **AND** COPY --from statements SHALL transfer artifacts correctly\n- **AND** final image SHALL be minimal and secure\n- **AND** build SHALL follow AR-032 specifications\n\n### Requirement: Development tool targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide development tool targets for managing local development environments.\n\n#### Scenario: dev target starts development environment\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with Docker Compose configuration\n- **WHEN** running `make dev`\n- **THEN** development services SHALL be started\n- **AND** services SHALL be accessible on expected ports\n- **AND** startup logs SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** environment SHALL be ready for development\n\n#### Scenario: dev-up target starts all development services\n- **GIVEN** the docker-compose.dev.yml configuration\n- **WHEN** running `make dev-up`\n- **THEN** Docker Compose SHALL start all services\n- **AND** services SHALL be started in detached mode\n- **AND** service status SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** all services SHALL be healthy\n\n#### Scenario: dev-down target stops all development services\n- **GIVEN** running development services\n- **WHEN** running `make dev-down`\n- **THEN** Docker Compose SHALL stop all services\n- **AND** containers SHALL be removed\n- **AND** networks SHALL be removed\n- **AND** volumes SHALL be removed (or preserved based on config)\n\n#### Scenario: dev-logs target shows development service logs\n- **GIVEN** running development services\n- **WHEN** running `make dev-logs`\n- **THEN** logs from all services SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** logs SHALL follow in real-time\n- **AND** timestamps SHALL be included\n- **AND** log level SHALL be appropriate (debug/info)\n\n#### Scenario: watch target monitors file changes\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with source code\n- **WHEN** running `make watch`\n- **THEN** file watcher SHALL be started\n- **AND** changes to Go files SHALL trigger rebuild\n- **AND** changes to Python files SHALL trigger reload\n- **AND** notifications SHALL be displayed for changes\n\n#### Scenario: run target starts local development server\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI or server components\n- **WHEN** running `make run`\n- **THEN** the development server SHALL be started\n- **AND** the server SHALL listen on default port\n- **AND** server logs SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** the server SHALL respond to requests\n\n### Requirement: Documentation targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide documentation targets for generating and serving project documentation.\n\n#### Scenario: docs target generates project documentation\n- **GIVEN** the documentation source files\n- **WHEN** running `make docs`\n- **THEN** documentation SHALL be generated\n- **AND** output SHALL be placed in docs/build/ directory\n- **AND** all documentation files SHALL be processed\n- **AND** generation SHALL complete successfully\n\n#### Scenario: docs-serve target starts documentation server\n- **GIVEN** generated documentation\n- **WHEN** running `make docs-serve`\n- **THEN** a local web server SHALL be started\n- **AND** documentation SHALL be accessible at http://localhost:8000\n- **AND** server logs SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** hot reload SHALL be enabled\n\n#### Scenario: docs-build target builds static documentation site\n- **GIVEN** the documentation source files\n- **WHEN** running `make docs-build`\n- **THEN** a static site SHALL be built\n- **AND** the site SHALL be production-ready\n- **AND** all assets SHALL be optimized\n- **AND** build artifacts SHALL be in docs/build/\n\n### Requirement: Dependency management targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive dependency management targets for Go and Python projects.\n\n#### Scenario: deps target downloads all dependencies\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make deps`\n- **THEN** `make deps-go` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** `make deps-python` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** all dependencies SHALL be downloaded\n- **AND** dependency status SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: deps-go target downloads Go dependencies\n- **GIVEN** the go.mod file\n- **WHEN** running `make deps-go`\n- **THEN** go mod download SHALL be executed\n- **AND** all Go module dependencies SHALL be downloaded\n- **AND** dependencies SHALL be cached\n- **AND** download status SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: deps-python target downloads Python dependencies\n- **GIVEN** the requirements.txt or pyproject.toml file\n- **WHEN** running `make deps-python`\n- **THEN** pip install SHALL be executed\n- **AND** all Python dependencies SHALL be installed\n- **AND** installed packages SHALL be listed\n- **AND** installation SHALL complete successfully\n\n#### Scenario: deps-update target updates all dependencies\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make deps-update`\n- **THEN** Go dependencies SHALL be updated (go get -u)\n- **AND** Python dependencies SHALL be updated (pip install --upgrade)\n- **AND** go mod tidy SHALL be run\n- **AND** updated packages SHALL be listed\n\n#### Scenario: deps-verify target verifies dependency integrity\n- **GIVEN** downloaded dependencies\n- **WHEN** running `make deps-verify`\n- **THEN** go mod verify SHALL be executed\n- **AND** Go dependency checksums SHALL be verified\n- **AND** Python dependencies SHALL be checked for integrity\n- **AND** verification results SHALL be displayed\n\n### Requirement: Version and release targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide version and release targets for managing project versions and releases.\n\n#### Scenario: version target displays version information\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make version`\n- **THEN** project version SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** Go version SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** Git commit SHA SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** build timestamp SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: release target creates a release version\n- **GIVEN** a prepared AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make release VERSION=1.0.0`\n- **THEN** all binaries SHALL be built in release mode\n- **THEN** Docker images SHALL be built and tagged\n- **AND** artifacts SHALL be packaged for distribution\n- **AND** release notes SHALL be generated\n\n#### Scenario: tag target creates Git tag for current version\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with changes committed\n- **WHEN** running `make tag VERSION=v1.0.0`\n- **THEN** a Git tag SHALL be created with the version\n- **AND** an annotated tag SHALL be created with release notes\n- **AND** tag SHALL be pushed to remote repository\n- **AND** tag creation SHALL be confirmed\n\n### Requirement: Help and metadata targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide self-documenting help and metadata targets.\n\n#### Scenario: help target displays all available targets\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make help`\n- **THEN** all available targets SHALL be listed\n- **AND** each target SHALL have a description\n- **AND** output SHALL be color-coded for readability\n- **AND** usage information SHALL be included\n\n#### Scenario: help target parses target comments\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile with target comments\n- **WHEN** running `make help`\n- **THEN** awk SHALL parse target comments (##)\n- **AND** help text SHALL be extracted from comments\n- **AND** help SHALL be automatically generated from code\n- **AND** no manual help text maintenance is required\n\n#### Scenario: list target lists all targets\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make list`\n- **THEN** all .PHONY targets SHALL be listed\n- **AND** target names SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** descriptions SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** list shall be alphabetically sorted\n\n#### Scenario: info target displays project build information\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube project\n- **WHEN** running `make info`\n- **THEN** project name SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** build directory SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** Go version SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** Python version SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** Docker registry SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** all Makefile variables SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: vars target displays all Makefile variables\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile with defined variables\n- **WHEN** running `make vars`\n- **THEN** all Makefile variables SHALL be listed\n- **AND** variable values SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** variable types SHALL be indicated\n- **AND** overridden variables SHALL be highlighted\n\n### Requirement: Variable configuration and overrides\n\nThe system SHALL support comprehensive variable configuration and overrides for flexible builds.\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile variables have sensible defaults\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the variable definitions\n- **THEN** GO_VERSION SHALL default to 1.24\n- **AND** PYTHON_VERSION SHALL default to 3.11\n- **AND** BUILD_DIR SHALL default to bin\n- **AND** BUILD_MODE SHALL default to dev\n- **AND** IMAGE_NAME SHALL default to agentcube\n\n#### Scenario: Variables can be overridden via environment\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile with default variables\n- **WHEN** setting environment variables (e.g., GO_VERSION=1.23)\n- **THEN** the environment variable SHALL override the default\n- **AND** the overridden value SHALL be used in the build\n- **AND** override SHALL be confirmed in output\n\n#### Scenario: Variables can be overridden via command line\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile with default variables\n- **WHEN** passing variables on command line (e.g., make build GO_VERSION=1.23)\n- **THEN** the command-line variable SHALL override the default\n- **AND** the overridden value SHALL be used in the build\n- **AND** override SHALL be confirmed in output\n\n#### Scenario: Color variables are defined for output\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the color variables\n- **THEN** BLUE variable SHALL be defined for informational output\n- **AND** GREEN variable SHALL be defined for success output\n- **AND** YELLOW variable SHALL be defined for warning output\n- **AND** RED variable SHALL be defined for error output\n- **AND** NC variable SHALL be defined to reset color\n\n### Requirement: .PHONY declarations\n\nThe system SHALL properly declare all virtual targets as .PHONY to avoid conflicts with files.\n\n#### Scenario: All build targets are declared as .PHONY\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the .PHONY declarations\n- **THEN** build SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** build-go SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** build-python SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** all individual component build targets SHALL be .PHONY\n\n#### Scenario: All test targets are declared as .PHONY\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the .PHONY declarations\n- **THEN** test SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** test-go SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** test-python SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** all test targets SHALL be .PHONY\n\n#### Scenario: All quality targets are declared as .PHONY\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the .PHONY declarations\n- **THEN** lint SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** format SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** check SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** all quality targets SHALL be .PHONY\n\n#### Scenario: All clean targets are declared as .PHONY\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the .PHONY declarations\n- **THEN** clean SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** clean-all SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** all clean targets SHALL be .PHONY\n\n#### Scenario: All Docker targets are declared as .PHONY\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the .PHONY declarations\n- **THEN** docker-build SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** docker-push SHALL be declared as .PHONY\n- **AND** all Docker targets SHALL be .PHONY\n\n### Requirement: Default target\n\nThe system SHALL set an appropriate default target that provides guidance to users.\n\n#### Scenario: Default target is set to help\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the .DEFAULT_GOAL variable\n- **THEN** .DEFAULT_GOAL SHALL be set to help\n- **AND** running `make` without arguments SHALL display help\n- **AND** users SHALL be guided to available targets\n\n#### Scenario: Default target provides clear guidance\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make` without arguments\n- **THEN** help information SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** common targets SHALL be highlighted\n- **AND** usage examples SHALL be provided\n- **AND** users SHALL understand how to proceed\n\n### Requirement: Error handling and validation\n\nThe system SHALL provide robust error handling and input validation.\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile validates required tools\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** running a target that requires a tool\n- **THEN** the tool's existence SHALL be checked\n- **AND** a clear error message SHALL be displayed if tool is missing\n- **AND** the error message SHALL include installation instructions\n- **AND** the build SHALL fail with appropriate exit code\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile validates environment\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** running a target that requires specific conditions\n- **THEN** environment SHALL be validated\n- **AND** required variables SHALL be checked\n- **AND** paths SHALL be validated\n- **AND** clear errors SHALL be displayed for invalid state\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile provides informative error messages\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** a build or test fails\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be displayed in red color\n- **AND** the error SHALL include file and line number\n- **AND** the error SHALL suggest a fix or next step\n- **AND** the error SHALL be easy to understand\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile handles missing dependencies gracefully\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** running a target with missing dependencies\n- **THEN** the missing dependency SHALL be identified\n- **AND** a helpful error message SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** instructions to install the dependency SHALL be provided\n- **AND** the build SHALL fail with appropriate exit code\n\n### Requirement: Cross-platform compatibility\n\nThe system SHALL be compatible with Linux, macOS, and provide guidance for Windows.\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile works on Linux\n- **GIVEN** a Linux system with required tools\n- **WHEN** running any Makefile target\n- **THEN** the target SHALL execute successfully\n- **AND** paths SHALL be handled correctly\n- **AND** commands SHALL be compatible with Linux\n- **AND** output SHALL be correctly formatted\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile works on macOS\n- **GIVEN** a macOS system with required tools\n- **WHEN** running any Makefile target\n- **THEN** the target SHALL execute successfully\n- **AND** paths SHALL be handled correctly (handling case sensitivity)\n- **AND** commands SHALL be compatible with macOS\n- **AND** BSD sed differences SHALL be handled\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile uses portable commands\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining the commands used\n- **THEN** portable commands SHALL be used (e.g., rm instead of del)\n- **AND** command options SHALL be portable across platforms\n- **AND** platform-specific logic SHALL use conditionals\n- **AND** GNU Make features SHALL be used appropriately\n\n### Requirement: Performance optimization\n\nThe system SHALL optimize build performance through caching, parallelism, and incremental builds.\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile supports parallel execution\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** running with -j flag (make -j build)\n- **THEN** independent targets SHALL run in parallel\n- **AND** build time SHALL be reduced\n- **AND** no race conditions SHALL occur\n- **AND** parallel execution SHALL be safe\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile tracks dependencies for incremental builds\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** rebuilding after a source file change\n- **THEN** only affected targets SHALL be rebuilt\n- **AND** unchanged targets SHALL use cached results\n- **AND** build time SHALL be faster than full build\n- **AND** dependency chain SHALL be correct\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile uses build cache for Go\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** building Go code\n- **THEN** Go build cache SHALL be utilized\n- **AND** unchanged packages SHALL use cache\n- **AND** cache hit messages SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** build time SHALL be optimized\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile uses build cache for Docker\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** building Docker images\n- **THEN** Docker layer cache SHALL be utilized\n- **AND** unchanged layers SHALL use cache\n- **AND** cache hit messages SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** build time SHALL be optimized\n\n---\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nThis delta specification defines a new Makefile build system for the AgentCube project. The Makefile provides a unified interface for building, testing, and managing the project, but does not change the underlying build processes. Existing build scripts and CI/CD configurations can continue to work, and developers can adopt the Makefile targets at their own pace. The Makefile is an additional interface that simplifies and standardizes build operations without breaking existing workflows.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis delta specification depends on:\n- GNU Make 4.0+ (Make execution engine)\n- Go 1.24+ (for building AgentCube Go components)\n- Python 3.11+ (for building AgentCube Python SDK)\n- Docker 20.10+ (for container image builds)\n- golangci-lint 1.50+ (for Go lint)\n- ruff 0.1+ (for Python lint)\n- black 23.0+ (for Python formatting)\n- pytest 7.0+ (for Python testing)\n- Base design document: `design.md`\n- Base specification document: `spec.md`\n- AR: AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (for Docker build integration)\n\n## Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This delta specification defines a new Makefile build system that provides a unified interface for project management. The Makefile does not change existing build processes, output formats, or runtime behavior. It simplifies and standardizes build operations without breaking any existing functionality, workflows, or deployments. Existing build scripts and CI/CD configurations can continue to work alongside the new Makefile targets.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Dependency Verification**: The Makefile includes `go mod verify` and similar checks for Python dependencies to ensure dependency integrity and prevent supply chain attacks.\n2. **No Secrets in Build Artifacts**: The Makefile ensures that no secrets or credentials are embedded in build artifacts or Docker images through proper .dockerignore configuration.\n3. **Secure Build Defaults**: Release mode builds strip debug information and use hardened build flags to produce production-ready binaries.\n4. **Non-Root Container Execution**: Docker build targets configure containers to run as non-root users, reducing the impact of container escape vulnerabilities.\n5. **Minimal Attack Surface**: Multi-stage Docker builds (from AR-032) produce minimal runtime images with reduced attack surface.\n6. **Build Isolation**: The Makefile uses isolated build environments and clean targets to prevent cross-contamination between builds.\n7. **Version Pinning**: Dependency management targets encourage using fixed versions to ensure reproducible and secure builds.\n8. **Lint Checks**: Lint targets help identify potential security issues and code quality problems before deployment.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Build Tests\n- Verify all build targets complete successfully\n- Verify build artifacts are placed in correct locations\n- Verify cross-platform builds work correctly\n- Verify release mode produces optimized binaries\n- Verify incremental builds use cache correctly\n\n### Test Execution Tests\n- Verify test targets execute all tests\n- Verify test coverage is collected and reported\n- Verify test-race detects race conditions\n- Verify parallel test execution works correctly\n- Verify specific package/path selection works\n\n### Code Quality Tests\n- Verify lint targets detect issues correctly\n- Verify format targets format code according to standards\n- Verify check target runs all quality checks\n- Verify lint/format exit codes are correct\n- Verify specific file selection works\n\n### Clean Tests\n- Verify clean targets remove all artifacts\n- Verify clean-all removes artifacts and caches\n- Verify clean targets use .NOTPARALLEL correctly\n- Verify no artifacts remain after clean-all\n- Verify clean targets are safe to run multiple times\n\n### Docker Build Tests\n- Verify Docker images build successfully\n- Verify multi-stage builds are used correctly\n- Verify images are tagged correctly\n- Verify push and tag operations work\n- Verify multi-arch builds work correctly\n\n### Dependency Management Tests\n- Verify deps target downloads all dependencies\n- Verify deps-update updates dependencies correctly\n- Verify deps-verify checks dependency integrity\n- Verify dependency errors are handled gracefully\n- Verify dependency caching works\n\n### Development Tool Tests\n- Verify dev targets start services correctly\n- Verify watch monitors file changes\n- Verify run starts development server\n- Verify logs are displayed correctly\n- Verify services are accessible on expected ports\n\n### Help and Metadata Tests\n- Verify help target displays all targets\n- Verify help is auto-generated from comments\n- Verify info target displays correct information\n- Verify vars target lists all variables\n- Verify default target is set to help\n\n### Variable Override Tests\n- Verify environment variable overrides work\n- Verify command-line overrides work\n- Verify default values are sensible\n- Verify color variables work correctly\n- Verify override confirmation is displayed\n\n### Error Handling Tests\n- Verify missing tool errors are clear\n- Verify environment validation works\n- Verify error messages are informative\n- Verify missing dependencies are handled gracefully\n- Verify exit codes are appropriate\n\n### Cross-Platform Tests\n- Verify Makefile works on Linux\n- Verify Makefile works on macOS\n- Verify portable commands are used\n- Verify path handling is correct on each platform\n- Verify platform-specific logic works correctly\n\n### Performance Tests\n- Measure full build time\n- Measure incremental build time\n- Measure parallel build speedup\n- Verify cache utilization\n- Verify build times meet expectations\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test Makefile in CI/CD pipeline\n- Verify Makefile integrates with Docker Compose\n- Verify Makefile works with Git hooks\n- Verify Makefile integrates with IDE build systems\n- Verify end-to-end workflows work correctly\n\n### Documentation Tests\n- Verify all targets have help comments\n- Verify help output is readable\n- Verify documentation is accurate\n- Verify examples are correct\n- Verify .makefiles/ sub-Makefiles are documented","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884136149,"end":1775884136159}}}}
